---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---
<MarketingLayout title="FAQ | FrontDoor Web Co." description="Answers for local business owners considering a professional website launch.">
  <section class="content-section"><div class="container prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
    <h1>Questions before investing in a better website</h1>
  </div></section>
  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container faq-grid">
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>What makes this worth $3,500+?</h2><p>The package includes strategy, copy structure, design polish, local SEO basics, contact flow, deployment, and revision time. It is built to help prospects understand and trust the business faster.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>How much do I need to provide?</h2><p>Bring business details, service notes, locations, photos if available, testimonials, and the best way for prospects to contact you. The project turns those inputs into a clear site.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>Can this grow later?</h2><p>Yes. The first launch can be expanded with service pages, city pages, new galleries, seasonal promotions, and stronger proof over time.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>Do you handle hosting?</h2><p>Yes. The launch can be deployed to a static host such as GitHub Pages, Cloudflare Pages, or Netlify.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>What if I do not have website copy?</h2><p>That is common. We can start with intake questions, rough notes, service details, and a short interview so the site still has clear, credible copy.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>Can you write the copy for me?</h2><p>Yes. Guided copywriting and full copy plus positioning can be added when you need help turning facts, services, and proof into website-ready pages.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>What do you need from me to write the copy?</h2><p>We need accurate facts, main services, service area, photos or proof if available, reviews or testimonials if you have them, and honest answers about why customers choose you.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>Do I need to be a good writer?</h2><p>No. You bring the real business details. We help organize the message, clean up the tone, and shape the copy so prospects can understand and trust the business.</p></article>
      <article class="faq-card"><h2>Do you guarantee results?</h2><p>No. We do not guarantee sales or make false claims. The goal is a clearer, more trustworthy website with fact-checked copy and practical calls to action.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
